---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = 'July 23, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | Wu Xing Wellness"
  description="What cookies Wu Xing Wellness uses, why, and how to manage or disable them."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--ink-faint);font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        This Cookie Policy explains how Wu Xing Wellness uses cookies and similar technologies on
        fiveelementsbalance.com. It supports our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What is a cookie?</h2>
      <p>
        A cookie is a small text file a website stores in your browser. It helps the site remember things like
        your preferences or how you use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Types of cookies we use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — needed for basic site function. They cannot be turned off.</li>
        <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> — used by Google AdSense and partners to show relevant ads and measure their performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate cookies</strong> — set by programs such as Amazon Associates so that referrals can be credited.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — if used, to understand aggregated traffic in order to improve content.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-party advertisers</h2>
      <p>
        Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your visits to this and other
        sites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visits.
        You can opt out at
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.
        Third-party vendors may also be listed at
        <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info/choices</a>
        for opt-out options.
      </p>

      <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> Most browsers let you block or delete cookies in their settings.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-out tools:</strong> Use the links above to opt out of personalised advertising.</li>
        <li><strong>Note:</strong> Blocking advertising cookies does not remove all ads; it makes them less relevant.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy as our use of cookies changes. Check the date above for the latest version.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a> with any cookie questions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
